<TITLE> Two additional IGPs made officers on special duty </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July (bdnews24.com) - Additional inspectors general of police SM Mizanur Rahman and ABM Bazlur Rahman have been made officers on special duty, the establishment ministry said in a statement Sunday. Mizanur was the director general of the Rapid Action Battalion while Bazlur was the commissioner of Dhaka Metropolitan Police before the emergency government came to power in January. In another development, joint secretary Habibur Rahman, an OSD, was appointed to the tax ombudsman's office as registrar while joint secretary Kamal Uiddn Ahmed, another OSD, would work for the information ministry, the ministry said. bdnew
